### Interactive Aquarium Guide

You can feed the fish and watch them react. Here’s how it works:

*   **Feeding the Fish:** Simply **left-click** anywhere inside the aquarium tank. A piece of fish food will appear at that location. You can click multiple times to add more food.
*   **Fish Behavior:** Each fish will automatically identify and swim toward the food piece that is closest to it. They swim faster when chasing food.
*   **Eating & Resuming:** When a fish gets close enough to a food piece, it will eat it, and the food disappears. Once all food pieces are gone, the fish will return to their normal, relaxed swimming pattern.

Here is the single-file HTML clock application code. It creates a minimalist wall clock with a smooth second hand, showing the time and date for China Standard Time.
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no">
  <title>MINIMAL · WALL CLOCK</title>
  <style>
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      min-height: 100vh;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      background: #f2f5f9;
      font-family: 'Inter', 'Segoe UI', 'Helvetica Neue', system-ui, sans-serif;
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    /* clock container — high-end, 3D depth, white dial */
    .clock {
      position: relative;
      width: 360px;
      height: 360px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: #ffffff;
      box-shadow: 
        0 20px 35px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15),
        0 8px 12px -6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08),
        inset 0 -3px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
      border: 2px solid #3d3d3d;
      transition: box-shadow 0.2s;
      /* make sure clock is a circle */
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    /* scale wrapper: 60 ticks, CSS generated */
    .scale {
      position: absolute;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      border-radius: 50%;
      will-change: transform;
    }

    /* each tick is a small rectangle, rotated around center */
    .tick {
      position: absolute;
      top: 4px;
      left: 50%;
      width: 4px;
      height: 16px;
      background: #b0b8c0;
      transform-origin: 50% 176px;  /* 360/2 - 4 = 176 (center offset) */
      border-radius: 4px;
      transition: background 0.1s;
    }

    /* thick & dark for hour marks (every 5th tick) */
    .tick.hour-tick {
      width: 6px;
      height: 24px;
      background: #2c2f33;
      top: 2px;                     /* raise a bit to align */
      transform-origin: 50% 178px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 0.5px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    }

    /* numbers: 12, 3, 6, 9 (minimalist, absolute) */
    .number {
